https://github.com/splunk/splunk-connect-for-kubernetes



*****INSTALL HELM******
	Download & install Helm easy script:
		curl -fsSL -o get_helm.sh https://raw.githubusercontent.com/helm/helm/master/scripts/get-helm-3
		chmod 700 get_helm.sh
		./get_helm.sh

***add HELM repo (optional will give you access to several Applications to log :D)****
	helm repo add stable https://kubernetes-charts.storage.googleapis.com
	helm repo update



****INSTALL SCK 1.4.1*****
	Creat Namespace for SCK
		kubectl create ns sck

	Review sck.yaml for additional parameters (like Splunk HEC endpoint)
	Install SCK chart	
		helm install sck -n sck -f sck.yaml splunk-connect-for-kubernetes-1.4.1.tgz 
	Verify
		kubectl get po -n sck 
